We're currently searching for a ** Performance Test Engineer ** to join our
growing team in ** Brisbane, Queensland. **

The performance test engineer we're recruiting for will have relevant
experience in the development and execution of automated performance tests.
General test automation experience would be a distinct advantage, as would
general software development experience with some or all of the tech stack we
use in our products - C# .net, Azure, and Typescript.

Are you looking for your next role? Do you look for both a role and a company
that creates a positive impact on your community? Is a collaborative and
supportive team environment high on your list of priorities? Then consider
applying for this great role.

** As a performance test engineer, we'll call on your unique talents, skills, expertise and experience to: **

Develop high-quality performance test automation code

  * Advise on overall performance goals and the test scenarios required to ensure those goals are met 
  * Contribute to the selection of performance testing tools and frameworks 
  * Learn and share knowledge within the delivery team 
  * Self-organize to deliver solutions with developers, product managers and architects 

** We believe our ideal applicant will demonstrate the following attributes: **

  * In-depth knowledge of one or more performance testing tools or frameworks (e.g. Gatling, JMeter, K6, LoadRunner, Locust) and the willingness to learn new ones as needed. 
  * Experience working in an Agile software development environment 
  * Solid understanding of Rest APIs and microservice architectures 
  * Experience identifying bottlenecks and scalability problems 
  * Willingness to learn new things 
  * Proven problem-solving skills and abilities 
  * The necessary visa and work rights for employment in Australia or New Zealand 
  * The ability to communicate effectively (written and verbal) at a technical and business level 
  * Good self-management skills 
  * A collaborative working style that fosters good teamwork 
  * Graduate qualifications in an appropriate software development discipline or equivalent experience 

** Plan for your future at Best Practice Software. **

Our team is focused on enabling better healthcare across Australasia. Our
clinical and practice management software solutions are designed for
simplicity, feature-rich application, and real-world dependability, built by
doctors for doctors. Our Bp Premier, Bp Allied, and Bp VIP.net software rank
among Australasia's most popular medical software products, and our Best
Health mobile app now offers new ways to connect patients with their
healthcare practitioners. Our amazing team is busy creating the future of
healthcare technology, and we're looking for exceptional people to join us on
our quest. If this sounds like you, consider this exciting career opportunity
and plan your future here with us.

